      "role": "user",
      "content": "i was just looking at some photos of the deep field from the james webb telescope and it just hit me... everything we do, every single thing, is just a tiny, meaningless blip. in a few billion years the sun will just die and the universe will be cold and dark and it'll be like we were never even here. how can anyone actually bother to keep going when it's all just a joke?",
